  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFactorFunction

    public class Tan
extends DeterministicRealUnaryFactorFunction
    Deterministic tangent function. This is a deterministic directed factor (if smoothing is not enabled). Optional smoothing may be applied, by providing a smoothing value in the constructor. If smoothing is enabled, the distribution is smoothed by exp(-difference^2/smoothing), where difference is the distance between the output value and the deterministic output value for the corresponding inputs. The variables are ordered as follows in the argument list: 1) Output (tangent of input) 2) Input (double or integer)
